\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. H. graveolens} (Bieb.) Sweet,{\i  Hort. Brit.} 223 (1826). Like {\b 13} but sweet-smelling; stems arising from slender, creeping underground stolons; indumentum laxer, villous-lanate and plant often yellowish-green; basal leaves distinctly 3-veined, the upper cauline often apiculate; outer florets female.{\i  Damp mountain grassland and open pineforest. Krym.} Rs (K). ({\i S.W. Asia.})
